The paper deals with a problem in graph theory, specifically the reassembling of graphs. This problem has applications in network analysis. The paper discusses the linear reassembling of graphs, which involves splicing edges in a specific order. The paper uses mathematical proofs to show the polynomial reducibility of the optimization problems involved in linear reassembling to known NP-hard problems in graph theory. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
